==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remand
<hw>Re*mand"</hw> <pr>(r?-m?nd")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Remanded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Remanding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>remander</ets> to send word again, L. <ets>remandare</ets>; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>mandare</ets> to commit, order, send word. See
<er>Mandate</er>.]</ety> <def>To recommit; to send back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Remand</qex> it to its former place.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then were they <qex>remanded</qex> to the cage again.</q>
<rj><qau>Bunyan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remand</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Remand
<hw>Re*mand"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of remanding; the order
for recommitment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remandment</ent>⟦br⟧
